column5: Twas the night before Xmas and all 'cross the ice, The walleye were biting, Soooo very nice!VIDEOhttps://youtu.be/Kxhxj6ss-jA
Looks like a good time was had by all! Nice video. Later, Jay

Strange....I worked Christmas day, at a husky refinery, as close to Canada as I would be on that day. It was a beautiful morning here, clear blue skies. I remember walking out of a building at 9am and thinking to myself, if I lived or was in Canada today my biggest problem would be debating on lake trout, walleye, pike, crappie, etc....then I came to, and went back to work!
Love it man...now that deer season is over I can do some ice fishing down here in iowa
